<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27157BBFA17FFDACE22BE9FFA71F833" box="[1306,1433,1923,1945]" pageId="114" pageNumber="115" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
: Fig. 3: Indian Cay, Grand Bahama I. (ANSP 366927), 240x; Fig. 4: holotype, Devil’s Bay, Grenada (USNM 1291335), 1,000x. Figs. 5–6: 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA17FFDACA3DBEDBFDE3F87C" box="[261,523,1984,2006]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Decoradrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="114" pageNumber="115" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="interstincta" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA17FFDACA3DBEDBFDE3F87C" box="[261,523,1984,2006]" italics="true" pageId="114" pageNumber="115">Decoradrillia interstincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27157BBFA17FFDAC921BEDAFD7FF87C" box="[537,663,1984,2006]" pageId="114" pageNumber="115" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, &quot;Big Rocks&quot;, Utila I., Bay Is., Honduras (ANSP 464986), 250x &amp; 1,000x, respectively.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C32C6559FA16FFDBCBFFB983FE82FF52" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8936D2FA16FFDBCBFFB983FE82FF52" blockId="115.[151,1436,151,248]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA16FFDBCBFFB983FEA6FF05" bold="true" box="[199,334,152,175]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Etymology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA16FFDBCA6FB98CFE19FF1A" box="[343,497,151,176]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Decoradrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="115" pageNumber="277" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA16FFDBCA6FB98CFE19FF1A" box="[343,497,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Decoradrillia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA16FFDBC810B98CFC9EFF1A" box="[808,886,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">decora</emphasis>
(glorious, noble, adjective, feminine form) and Greek 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA16FFDBCBDDB9A7FEC3FF7F" box="[229,299,188,213]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Drillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="115" pageNumber="362" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA16FFDBCBDDB9A7FEC3FF7F" box="[229,299,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">drillia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(machine). The name was inspired by the striking color patterns exhibited by most of the species discovered to date.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
